detaileddescription.para:
The multiplication operator of the Bond means that Combine two Bond. So this operator is same as combineBond. The following code are same result: //bd1,bd2andbd3areBondobjects.
bd3=bd1.combineBond(bd2);
 //bd1,bd2andbd3areBondobjects.
bd3=bd1*bd2;

operator*=(const Bond &rhs), combineBond(const Bond &bd_in, const bool &is_grp) const

The multiplication assignment operator of the Bond means that Combine two Bond inplacely, So this operator is same as combineBond_. The following code are same result: //bd1andbd2areBondobjects.
bd1.combineBond_(bd2);
 //bd1andbd2areBondobjects.
bd1*=bd2;

operator*(const Bond &rhs) const, combineBond_(const Bond &bd_in, const bool &is_grp)
